<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-062-081 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 260 885</DOCID><JOURNAL>CommunicationsWeek  Sept 9 1991 n368 p13(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>SNAC satisfies IBM user appetites. (Sync Research Inc.'s StandardNetwork Architecture Network Access Controller for Token-Ring)(product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Depompa, Barbara.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>For those IBM corporate users that still have 3270 terminalcluster controllers on their local area networks (LANs), SyncResearch Inc's SNAC (Standard Network Architecture Network AccessController for Token-Ring) controller is a way of attaching thosecontrollers to new token-ring networks.andP;  The SNAC controllers canconnect non-programmable terminals such as the IBM 3274 and 4700to token-ring networks at a lower cost than it would take to buynew equipment.andP;  Each SNAC/TR can connect a minimum of four clustercontrollers.andP;  Before the SNAC/TR controller was introduced,corporate customers had to either upgrade their clustercontrollers to obtain token-ring connectivity, or to maintainexpensive synchronous data-link control transmission lines for theolder devices.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Sync Research Inc. (Products).andO;Product:   Sync Research SNA Network Access Controller for Token-Ring(Communications controller) (Product introduction)IBM 3270 Connection Card (Computer terminal emulator) (Equipmentand supplies).andO;Topic:     ConnectivityCommunications ControllersLocal area networksCluster controllers.andO;Feature:   illustrationchart.andO;Caption:   SNAC tides users over. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>